# Copy to .env.local for local testing, or set these as Environment Variables
# in your host's project settings for production (see CLAUDE.md → "Environment
# variables"). Both are optional — the site works fine with neither set; you
# just won't get analytics or the email capture form.

# Your GoatCounter counting endpoint (goatcounter.com → your site → Settings
# → the URL shown for "data-goatcounter", looks like https://CODE.goatcounter.com/count).
# Free for reasonable public use, no account limit like a trial. Only set
# this in production — leaving it unset locally means the analytics script
# never loads in dev, so nothing fires and nothing needs a mock.
PUBLIC_GOATCOUNTER_URL=https://stackverdict.goatcounter.com/count

# Where the "email me the deep-dive report" form on the results page submits
# to. We use Formspree by default (https://formspree.io) — create a form
# there and paste its endpoint URL here. Swap in any other form-backend
# service (Basin, Getform, ...) or your own — the code just does a plain
# fetch() POST with { email, source } as JSON.
PUBLIC_FORM_ENDPOINT=https://formspree.io/f/your-form-id
